    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="260"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d260">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State <persName type="from"
                            >Adee</persName> to Chargé <persName type="to">Moore</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-12-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 1, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 219.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of Mr.
                    Rockhill’s dispatch, No. 433, of October 17 last, inclosing copies of two notes
                    addressed by him to Prince Ch’ing regarding the proposed new Chinese mining
                    regulations, in the second of which he emphasizes the fact that the regulations
                    must be submitted to him for consideration before they may properly be put into
                    effect.</p>
                <p>The department approves Mr. Rockhill’s course in the matter.</p>
                <p>In this connection I inclose herewith a copy of a letter from Mr. F. W. Sutterle,
                    managing director of the American-Chinese Company, renewing his complaint of
                    delay on the part of the Chinese Government in promulgating the rules and
                        regulations.<note n="a" xml:id="d260fna">Not printed.</note> A copy of the
                    department’s answer is also inclosed.<note n="a" xml:id="d260fnb">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
